# Codenames Mobile — change log
# Every change is recorded here with its justification (newest at the bottom).

[2026-07-12] Web-parity batch 1 — bring the mobile client up to the web app's feature set.
  Justification: the mobile app was missing many controls/screens present on the web app; users
  asked for full parity ("each and every option, feature and functionality").

  - src/protocol.ts: added WORD_PACK_META and TIMER_OPTIONS (mirrors of the backend metadata) and the
      social DM types (PublicUser, DMView, ConversationView). Needed so the mobile lobby controls and
      DM UI use the same ids/labels the server expects.
  - src/hooks/useRoom.ts: added host lobby actions — setVariant, setWordPack, setTimer, setPrivate,
      resetTeams, randomizeTeams — emitting the existing server events (room:setVariant, room:setWordPack,
      settings:update, room:setPrivate, teams:reset, teams:randomize). These existed on web but not mobile.
  - src/components/Lobby.tsx: added a host-only "HOST CONTROLS" panel (game mode, word pack, turn timer,
      public/private, reset/randomize teams) matching the web lobby.
  - src/components/RulesModal.tsx (new): "How to play" modal, content mirrored from the web RulesModal.
  - src/screens/RoomScreen.tsx: added a Rules button in the room header that opens RulesModal.
  - src/auth.ts: added updateProfile() (PATCH /api/profile) so users can edit their display name; the
      reissued token is applied to the socket.
  - src/hooks/useSocial.ts: added DM actions — dmHistory, sendDm, markDmRead.
  - src/components/DMThread.tsx (new): direct-message conversation view with live delivery and
      sent/delivered/seen receipts, mirroring the web DM panel.
  - src/screens/AccountScreen.tsx: display-name editing UI; friends are now tappable to open a DM thread.

  Verification: `npx tsc --noEmit` passes (exit 0). On-device run pending (no simulator in this env).
